@database ToolbarClass
@index "Classes.guide/Main"

@Node Main "RxMUI - Toolbar Class"


Toolbar class    @{"Index" link "Classes.guide/Main"} @{"Super" link "AreaClass.guide/Main"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Toolbar class is used to create image buttons bars.

  Toolbar is a subclass of Toolbar.mcc so you must have
  Toolbar.mcc in MUI:Libs/MUI to use it. Toolbar.mcc is copyright
  of Benny Kjćr Nielsen.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

  Toolbar.rxmec is also an ARexx shared library.

  You don't have to worry about adding Toolbar.rxmec to the ARexx
  libraries list, because it is done automatically.

  @{b}TBNotify@{ub} - Adds a notification.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
  res = TBNotify(notifier,button,attr,value,target,method,parameters)
  <notifier/V>,<id/N>,<attr/V>,<value>,<target/V>,<method/V>,{parms}

  @{b}Function@{ub}
   Adds a notification from notifier, a Toolbar object button
   with id button, to target triggered by attr when it changes to
   value invoking method on target with parms.

   You may use this function only with Toolbar objects, when you
   want to set up a notify triggered by a Toolbar button.

   attr may be one of:
      o Active
      o Ghosted
      o Gone
      o Pressed

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
   notifier - the object that notifies
   id - the button id of the bar
   attr - the attribute that triggers the notification
   value - the value of attr that causes the notification
   target - the target of the notification. Specials values are:
      o _app - the application notifier belongs to
      o _win - the window notifier belongs to
      o _self - notifier itself
   method - a valid an indirect method to invoke on target
   parms - parameters for method

  @{b}Result@{ub}
   res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

   The function may fail if:
   [NO_OBJ] notifier or target not found
   [NO_METHOD] method is not valid for target
   [METHOD_NONOTIFY] method is direct-only
   [BAD_NOTIFY] the notification can't be added for some reason

  @{b}See@{ub}
   @{"Notification" LINK "Functions.guide/Notification"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Bar attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Description@{fg text}
  S I
  ARexx stem name, list of the buttons. If not supplied it is
  considered to be the object stem.

  @{fg shine}Help@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}Horiz@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}ImageGhost@{fg text}
  S I
  Name of the ghosted images file.

  @{fg shine}ImageNormal@{fg text}
  S I
  Name of the normal images file.

  @{fg shine}ImageSelect@{fg text}
  S I
  Name of the selected images file.

  @{fg shine}Path@{fg text}
  S I
  Path to the images files. If supplied, images files are
  considered relative to this path.

  @{fg shine}Qualifier@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Buttons attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Exclude@{fg text}
  N I
  Mutual exclude mask. E.g. if button 10 excludes buttons 4 and
  9, button 10 Exclude is 2**4+2**9

  @{fg shine}Flags@{fg text}
  S I
  One or more of:
     o Ghosted
     o Gone
     o Radio
     o Selected
     o Toggle

  @{fg shine}Help@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Text@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Type@{fg text}
  S I
  One of:
     o Button
     o Ignore
     o Space

  @{fg shine}Path@{fg text}
  S I
  Path to the images files. If supplied, images file are
  considered relative to this path.

  @{fg shine}Reusable@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}Description@{fg text}
  S I
  ARexx stem name, list of the buttons. If not supplied it is
  considered to be the object stem.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}TBKillNotify@{fg text}
  -
  Use this instead of KillNotify()

  @{fg shine}TBreload@{fg text}
  <ImageNormal/N>,<ImageSelect>,<ImageGhost>
  Changes images

  @{fg shine}TBSet@{fg text}
  <id/N>,<what>,<value/N>
  Sets what of button id to value.
  what is one of:
     o Ghosted
     o Gone
     o Selected

  @{fg shine}TBSetAll@{fg text}
  <what>,<value/N>
  Sets what of all the buttons to value.
  what is one of:
     o Ghosted
     o Gone
     o Selected

@EndNode

